When imagining learning objectives for VR apps, educators tend to think big.
&ldquo;Students can explore the whole universe!&rdquo;
&ldquo;They&rsquo;ll live in history!&rdquo;
&ldquo;It&rsquo;ll be like Magic School Bus, but in VR!&rdquo;
VR tends to inspire these flights of imagination because, well, that&rsquo;s what tech companies promise us. Also: it is technically possible to do all the things I just had hypothetical educators imagine. The catch, of course, is that developing for VR takes lots of time, money, and skill.
